                            <comment id="14608139" author="andie78" created="Tue, 30 Jun 2015 11:19:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That should be the matching files before upgrading.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14608331" author="philipthompson" created="Tue, 30 Jun 2015 14:05:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=blambov&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;blambov&quot;&gt;blambov&lt;/a&gt;, this looks like a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9654&quot; title=&quot;Failure to open sstable after upgrade to trunk&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-9654&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-9654&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, except it&apos;s happening from 2.1 - 2.2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Andie78&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Andie78&quot;&gt;Andie78&lt;/a&gt;, thank you for the detailed bug report. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14610399" author="yukim" created="Wed, 1 Jul 2015 14:48:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Andie78&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Andie78&quot;&gt;Andie78&lt;/a&gt;, do you have system.log that contains other log(not only ERROR)?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Especially, I&apos;m looking for compaction logs, like &lt;tt&gt;Compacting [SSTableReader...]&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;Compacted 4 sstables to...&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14610418" author="andie78" created="Wed, 1 Jul 2015 15:04:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Whole system.log of 2.2.0-rc1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14610612" author="yukim" created="Wed, 1 Jul 2015 16:39:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, but it didn&apos;t contains the logs that I expected. Do you have INFO level logs as well?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14610628" author="yukim" created="Wed, 1 Jul 2015 16:52:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think I found the problem though.&lt;br/&gt;
It is indeed caused by the fact that old secondary index files are not properly handled after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6962&quot; title=&quot;examine shortening path length post-5202&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-6962&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-6962&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently, directory for secondary index is deteremined to be the same as old directory format (ks/cf, instead of ks/cf/.idxname) since it is upgrade.&lt;br/&gt;
Operation like compaction can rewrite old secondary index files to new file name which does not have ks and cf name in it, and placed it the old directory.&lt;br/&gt;
That mixes up secondary index files with its parent data files.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14611075" author="yukim" created="Wed, 1 Jul 2015 22:09:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I pushed patch to: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/yukim/cassandra/tree/9687&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/yukim/cassandra/tree/9687&lt;/a&gt; (tests are still running)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6962&quot; title=&quot;examine shortening path length post-5202&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-6962&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-6962&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduces new directory structure for secondary index.&lt;br/&gt;
If you create index (say, idx on ks.cf) in 2.2+, then you have:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;/path_to_data_dir/ks/cf-cfid/.idx
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which is fine, but if you already have index files in 2.0 or 2.1 and then upgrade to 2.2, you still have those SSTables in&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;/path_to_data_dir/ks/cf-cfid/
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and newly created files which don&apos;t have ks and cf names in file name try to stay in that same directory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch fixes the issue by forcing new directory structure for upgrades, and move the files to new directory at the beginning.&lt;br/&gt;
Also, snapshot and backup directory weren&apos;t handled correctly, so they are also fixed and new unit tests are added.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14611988" author="andie78" created="Thu, 2 Jul 2015 13:59:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;C* is always generating la-1-big.* which cause C* stopping on the next start although I delete them before start. No old matching &amp;gt;jb-1&amp;lt; files in the folder. The &amp;gt;jb-1642&amp;lt; files - including la-1642-big-Index.db in the same folder - are accepted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;system.log&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;ERROR [SSTableBatchOpen:1] 2015-07-02 15:39:08,888 SSTableReader.java:432 - Cannot open D:\Programme\Cassandra\data\data\nieste\niesteinverters\la-1-big; partitioner org.apache.cassandra.dht.LocalPartitioner does not match system partitioner org.apache.cassandra.dht.Murmur3Partitioner.  Note that the &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;default&lt;/span&gt; partitioner starting with Cassandra 1.2 is Murmur3Partitioner, so you will need to edit that to match your old partitioner &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; upgrading.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
